<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="1JN" stage="Rev" version="A">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 04:08:34Z" when="2009-10-02 04:08:34Z" stage="Draft">drafted by Pdt. Max Jacob; revised by Barbara Grimes; reworked in Darwin with June, Mus, Tresi in August 2005; another pass with Barbara &amp; team, discussing Chuck's comments (separate file) in Sept 2005; Ex. Summ. HCE, GNT, NRSV, NLT, CEV, TH, IVP Bible Background Commentary; The Message, The Source; UNS checked by Mus &amp; June 16-18 Sept 2005 in Kupang; UNS suggestions evaluated by Chuck Oct 2005; BT by Barbara, Oct 2005, reviewed by Chuck [full comments/discussion saved in Kup-1YOH-BT-C.db file] many later stripped out for consultant check; final read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 11:20:33Z" when="2014-02-24 11:20:33Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: October 2004 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: Translation Con Rep Kupang Malay 1 John.doc; Taber Qs on 1-3 Jn CEG.doc</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-23 01:26:24Z" when="2015-01-23 01:26:24Z" stage="Rev">Smoothing read thru for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, rina, Oma at UBB. BackTrans also adjusted.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">1 Yohanis</p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">1 Yohanis<bt>1 Yohanis</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Yohanis pung surat yang partama<bt>Yohanis' first letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tulis so'al Yesus Kristus<bt>Yohanis writes about Yesus Kristus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Beta tulis ini surat so'al Tuhan Allah pung <span class="Italic">Kata-kata yang Bawa Idop</span>.<bt>I write this letter about God1's <span class="Italic">Words which Bring Life.</span> [DISCOURSE: typical eastern Indonesian discourse patterns have oral title before getting stuck into it. So we've set it off as a separate paragraph.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ini <span class="Italic">Kata-kata yang Bawa Idop</span> ni, su ada memang dari dunya pung mula-mula. Sakarang beta, deng beta pung tamán dong su lia sang Dia deng botong pung mata kapala sandiri. Botong su dengar sang Dia deng botong pung talinga sandiri. Deng botong su raba sang Dia deng botong pung tangan sandiri. Botong lia sang Dia bagitu,<bt>These <span class="Italic">Words which Bring Life</span> already existed beforehand from the world's beginning. Now I, and my friends have seen Him with our own eyes. We-exc have heard Him with our our own ears. And we-exc we have touched him with our own hands. We saw/watched Him in that way, [DISCOURSE: Location of "Word of Life": it is put at beginning of verse because RL narratives usually start off right away with background info--Who the story is about. (CEV also sticks last Gk clause Word of Life at beginning of verse.) Also in RL narratives and world view, it is ok (actually not just ok, but more interesting and more intriguing) to keep things partly veiled, and to talk indirectly about someone. So (consequently) it seems ok to stick with the Gk in not referring overtly to Jesus as the Word of Life. So no attempt has been made to overtly link The Word of Life with Jesus Christ yet (as in NLT and other translations). If s.o. doesn't get it right away, na, it is in the header. Four verbs: heard, seen, beheld, touched, CEV has only 3, combining see and beheld. KM puts see first because this is most naturally said first when trying to prove a first hand experience. It ranks higher as an evidential.] [EXEG: In the Gk “this we proclaim/declare” is not in vs. 1, but vs. 2. But because of how they have structured these two verses, NRSV and NIV have put it in vs. 1. Kupang has it in vs. 2, like the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arkhee: beginning akouoo: hear|i(1) (1) |rhoraoo:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">arkhee: beginning akouoo: hear<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>horaoo: see, catch sight of, notice heemoon: John and the other disciples, not the people getting the letter.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>theaomai: see, look at, behold, steady and deliberate gaze pselaphaoo: touch, feel, handle, grope for<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>logos: word, message zooe: life. HCE: Since the next verse picks up on "life" as something passed on to others, and drops the "word" theme, elaborating on the Word as "living" runs the paragraph into a dead end.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: That which was from the beginning, which we have heard, which we have seen with our eyes, which we have looked at and our hands have touched, concerning the word of life,</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:1</note><v n="2" />tagal Dia muncul datang di botong pung teng-tenga. Dolu Dia tenga deng Dia pung Bapa, ma sakarang Dia su kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang botong. Tagal itu, botong barani kasi tau sang bosong karmana manusia bisa dapa idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Te Dia ni, <span class="Italic">Kata-kata yang Bawa Idop.</span><bt>because He appeared coming into our-exc midst. Previously He lived/resided with His Father, but now He has shown Himself to us-exc. Because of that, we-exc dare to tell you-pl how humans can get true/real life that never ends. Cuz (elaboration) He, = <span class="Italic">Words which Bring Life.</span></bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phanerooo: be revealed, be shown, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">phanerooo: be revealed, be shown, be manifested, appear martureoo: testify, witness, declare, confirm<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>apaggelloo: declare, proclaim aioonios: eternal, everlasting<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: And the life was revealed, and we saw and testify and declare to you the eternal life which was with the Father and was shown to us.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:14</note><v n="3" />Botong mau kasi tau sang bosong, samua yang botong su lia, deng samua yang botong su dengar, ko bosong bisa satu hati deng botong. Te kotong samua su ta'ika deng Tuhan Allah deng Dia pung Ana yang Dia kirim datang, andia Yesus Kristus.<bt>We-exc want to tell all of you everything which we have seen, and everything which we have heard, so that you can be one liver (idiom; in.unity/harmony/accord) with us. Cuz/For (elaboration) we-inc all are already bound/linked with God1 and His Child whom He sent, who.is Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koinoonia: fellowship, association, communion, interaction, close"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">koinoonia: fellowship, association, communion, interaction, close relationship, have in common, be united, mutual relationship, partnership, participate with, sharing Khristou: first time in the letter, best place to introduce Jesus fully.<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: That which we have seen and heard we declare also to you, that you also may have fellowship with us. And our fellowship is with the Father and with his Son Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Jadi botong tulis ini surat, ko bekin sanáng bosong pung hati. Deng bagitu, botong pung hati ju tamba sanáng.<bt>So we-exc write this letter, to make your-pl livers (hearts) happy. And in.that.way, our-exc livers also increase in happiness. [EXEG: TEXT: Greek reading of “you-pl” rather than “we” is weak, and not followed by any recent translation. 'our' (our joy) is probably we-inclusive although some manuscripts say your joy (see note in NLT) The concept of our-inc is acheived here by having both you-pl and we-exc be happy // LEX: Greek /plerooo/ (make full, fulfill, complete, finish) is achieved here by the word /tamba/ "increase". = we were happy, but by writing this to you, you get happy and it makes us even happier. To try and force a word like "complete" together with "happy" produces a major collocational clash.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xara: joy plerooo: make full, fulfill,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">xara: joy plerooo: make full, fulfill, complete, finish<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: And we write these things [to you] that our joy may be complete.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang parcaya musti idop dalam taráng<bt>Believers must live in the light</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ajaran yang Yesus kasi tau sang botong, yang sakarang botong mau kasi tau sang bosong, andia bagini: Tuhan Allah tu, bae talalu. Dia sonde ada pung jahat sadiki ju. Te Dia sama ke taráng yang bacaya, yang sonde ada pung galáp sadiki ju.<bt>The teaching which Yesus told us-exc, which now we want to tell to you-pl, is like this: God1 (+whom you know about), is exceedingly good. He doesn't have even a little bit of evil. Cuz (elaboration) He is like light which shines, which doesn't have even a little bit of darkness. [EXEG to daughter translations: light = Ex. Summ: "symbolizes all ethically good qualities of God; first listed is goodness, but other credible ones include: holiness, purity, righteousness, truth; ES: What is meant by darkness'? It is the opposite of light/antithesis of all that God is -- a symbol for evil (general, deeds, way of life), untruthfulness, sin, error,]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aggelia: message, announcement phoos: light --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">aggelia: message, announcement phoos: light -- a forced metaphor in Pidgin, not self evident<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>skotia: darkness, gloom -- also a forced metaphor LITERALLY: And this is the message which we heard from him and declare to you, that God is light and there is no darkness at all in him.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Kalo kotong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong idop satu hati deng Tuhan,&gt;&gt; padahal kotong masi idop bekin hal jahat, na, itu sama ke kotong idop dalam galáp. Te kotong omong putar-balek, deng sonde idop iko jalan yang batúl.<bt>If we-inc speak saying, &lt;&lt;We-inc live one livered (idiom; in.unity/harmony/accord) with God2,&gt;&gt; but.in.actual.fact we-inc are still living doing evil things, na, that is the same as if we-inc live in the dark. Cuz (elaboration) we speak twisted-turned (idiom; deceptively), and do not live following the true/correct path/way.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peripateoo: walk around, go around, live"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">peripateoo: walk around, go around, live skotia: "da" would make it sound like a no-no list. Should be generic throughout the letters except when qualified.<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>pseudomai: lie; "bulai" is often transitive, but it has an intransitive use poieoo: do, practice<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>aletheia: truth. It needs to qualify something, rather than standing alone as a Greek abstract noun. LITERALLY: If we say that we have fellowship with him, and walk in darkness, we lie, and do not practice the truth.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma kalo kotong idop iko jalan yang batúl, kotong sama ke orang yang idop dalam Tuhan Allah pung taráng. Deng bagitu, kotong bisa idop satu hati, satu deng satu. Deng kotong pung hati jadi barisi, tagal Tuhan Allah pung Ana Yesus mati, deng Dia pung dara su hapus buang kotong pung sala dong samua.<bt>But if we-inc live following the correct path/way, we are like people who live in God1's light. In that way, we-inc can live one livered (in.unity/harmony/ accord) with each other. And our-inc livers become clean/pure/holy, because God1's Child Yesus died, and His blood has wiped away all our-inc wrongs. [EXEG: Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phoos: light. haima: blood|i(7) (7) |rkatharizoo:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">phoos: light. haima: blood<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>katharizoo: cleanse hamartia: sins we have committed, or sins we might potentially commit too? If anterior, then "da" and "wen" are OK.<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship with each other, and the blood of Jesus his Son cleanses us from all sin.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang idop dalam taráng, sonde idop bekin sala lai [\s2]<bt>People who live in the light, do not live/keep doing wrong anymore [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Kalo kotong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong sonde bekin sala,&gt;&gt; na, itu jadi tanda bilang, kotong su tipu kotong pung diri sandiri, deng sonde tau apa yang batúl.<bt>If we-inc speak saying, &lt;&lt;We-inc don't do wrong,&gt;&gt; na, that is a sign saying, we are deceiving ourselves, and do not know what is true/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="planaoo: deceive, mislead, fool, be led"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">planaoo: deceive, mislead, fool, be led astray, take the wrong road ouk estin en heemiin: is the truth absent from our thinking? our doing? how does it relate to "us"?<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: If we say that we do not have sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ma kalo kotong mangaku kotong pung sala, tantu Tuhan Allah yang ada pung hati lurus, ju bekin iko Dia pung janji deng hapus buang kotong pung sala, deng bekin barisi kotong pung hati.<bt>But If we-inc acknowledge/confess our-inc wrongs, surely God1, who has (a) straight/just liver, will also do according to His promise and wipe/erase away our wrongs, and make our livers clean/pure/holy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="homologeoo: confess, say the same thing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">homologeoo: confess, say the same thing about, acknowledge openly pistos: trustworthy, faithful, dependable, worthy of confidence. "God" needs to be repeated because the span for pronominal identification is different from English, and still different from Greek.<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>dikaios: just, righteous aphiemi: forgive, cancel a debt, removal of guilt. Usually phrased as a lexical doublet: let us go an take away our shame<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>katharizoo: cleanse, purify. Doesn't need a repeated auxiliary "goin", since these actions can be taken as two aspects of a single process. adikia: unrighteousness, wickedness, injustice<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: If we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins, and cleanse us from all unrighteousness.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kalo kotong omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong sonde parná bekin sala,&gt;&gt; na, itu kotong su bekin sang Tuhan Allah jadi tukang putar-balek! Te Dia su omong bilang, samua orang bekin sala abis. Deng kalo kotong omong bagitu, su jalás bilang, Dia pung Kata-kata sonde ada di kotong pung hati.<bt>If we-inc speak saying, &lt;&lt;We have never done wrong,&gt;&gt; na, that means we have made God1 become a habitual twister-turner (idiom; deceiver/liar). Cuz He has said that everyone does wrong. And it's clear that, His Words are not in our-inc livers. [EXEG: Ex. Summ: "Have not sinned': The claim in 1:8 denies having a sin nature, while the claim here denies having committed sinful acts.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heemarteekamen: any kind of sin. &quot;Da&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">heemarteekamen: any kind of sin. "Da" would be too restrictive. pseustes: liar<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>logos: word, message LITERALLY: If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Ana sayang dong! Beta tulis kasi tau ini samua, ko biar bosong sonde idop bekin sala lai. Ma andekata ada yang bekin sala, nanti ada yang bela kotong di Allah Bapa pung muka. Dia tu, Yesus Kristus, andia Orang Barisi yang Tuhan Allah su kirim datang di ini dunya.<bt>Beloved children! I write telling you all this, so that you don't live doing wrong anymore. But if perchance [+hypothetical] there is (someone) who does wrong, later there is one who will defend us-inc in front of Father God. He (+whom you know), is Yesus Kristus, who.is the Clean/Holy Person whom God1 has already sent into this world. [EXEG: VOCATIVES: Gk. vocatives at 1 Jn 2:1 ‘children’ [Gk teknia] (not literally ‘little children’ [NRSV] or ‘dear children’ [NLT] although those English translations are not inconsistent with John's style); 2:7 ‘beloved’; 2:12 ‘children’ [Gk teknia]; 2:13a ‘fathers/parents’; 2:13b ‘young men/people’; 2:14a ‘children’ [Gk paidia -recent research (e.g. Nyland) is finding that this term is much broader than ‘child/lad’, and can encompass adults and females in its usage in the NT, LXX and extra-biblical Koiné uses]; 2:14b ‘fathers/parents’; 2:14c ‘young men/people’; 2:18 ‘children’ [Gk paidia]; 2:28 ‘children’ [Gk teknia]; 3:2 ‘beloved’ [Gk agapetoi]; 3:7 ‘children’ [Gk teknia]; 3:13: ‘brothers/brothers and sisters’ [Gk adelphoi]; 3:18 ‘children’ [Gk teknia]; 3:21 ‘beloved’; 4:1 ‘beloved’; 4:4 ‘children’ [Gk teknia]; 4:7 ‘beloved’; 4:11 ‘beloved’; 5:21 ‘children’ [Gk teknia]; Structure: Gk can use vocatives sentence initial, medial, or final. Lgs around Timor can only use vocatives sentence initial - except for a few fixed phrases (as in 2:28, which may not be natural in daughter lgs). Semantics and referent tracking: Gk teknia ‘children’ really doesn't have ‘dear’ or ‘little’ as an inherent part of it's semantics. And just like Carson says too much should not be read into differences between Gk agapaw and philew (which are often used interchangeably), so too here I don't think we should read too much into the switch between teknia and paidia. To do so would result in overtranslation. In these lgs, to translate the Gk agapetoi ‘beloved’ as ‘friends’ (as in 3:2) would diminish/distance them in status and intimacy, whereas using the same term ‘beloved children’ is closer to the force of the Gk, indicating they are really special in John's eyes. Style: My sense of these languages is that 1) John uses vocatives way more than most people in this region would; 2) the sense of plain ‘children’ is a much more natural vocative in these lgs than heavy repetition of ‘dear children’; BUT 3) the repetition of ‘dear children’ does reflect John's unique and repetitious style of writing; HOWEVER 4) while it works in Kupang (sort of), it is probably forced and heavy in many daughter lgs, so given that the Gk does not have an explicit ‘dear’ anyway, I would support daughter translations using the lighter phrasing of just ‘children’ in many of these places.] [NOTE: My little children: although Greek has 'my' it is more natural in KM vocatives like this to leave it implied. // LEX: KeyT: bela kotong: /paraklétos/ appears to only appear here and in John, so no previous KM translation of it yet. // NOTE to daughter translations: Compare Righteous One in Acts 7:52.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teknion: little child. It's an old"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">teknion: little child. It's an old man writing to younger Christians whom he has been warmly encouraging for years. hamarteete: present durative. "Da" would make it sound too specific.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>parakletos: helper, intercessor, advocate, person who pleads another's cause, lawyer Khriston: the full identification here adds to the impact of the statement, and besides it's in a different rhetorical segment from the first use. But "Christ" is all that's needed in the section heading.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>dikaios: righteous, upright, just LITERALLY: My little [dear] children, I write these things to you so that you may not sin. But if anyone sins, we have an advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the righteous one.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia mati jadi korban kasi sang kotong, ko Tuhan Allah hapus buang kotong pung sala dong. Bukan cuma kasi kotong sandiri sa, ma kasi manusia samua di ini dunya ju.<bt>He died becoming a sacrifice for us-inc, so that God1 wipes/erases away our-inc wrongs. Not just for us-inc ourselves, but also for all the humans in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hilasmos: propitiation, expiation, sin offering, sin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">hilasmos: propitiation, expiation, sin offering, sin offering substitute, remove defilement/sin, atoning sacrifice, cleanse from defilement monos: only<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>holos: whole kosmos: world<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: And he is the propitiation for our sins, not only for ours, but also for the whole world.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang idop dalam taráng, bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta, lebe-lebe parenta so'al basayang [\s2]<bt>People who live in the light, do according to God1's command/s, especially the command about love [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Kotong tau bilang, kotong kanál bae deng Tuhan Allah, kalo kotong iko Dia pung parenta dong.<bt>We know that, we know God1 well, if we-inc follow/obey His commands. [NOTE to daughter translations: "know": Ex Summ: It means to be personally acquainted with God (many say deep/intimate is implied here), It is not talking about head knowledge /tau, mangarti/. But be careful about just using a neutral term equivalent to /kanál/ by itself, (to know s.o., their character, etc.) because it can have a strong sense 1) know s.o.'s character intimately, or a weak/shallow sense 2) You can kanál someone you met only briefly. Perhaps /kanál bae/ or /ta'ika/. Avoid the /babae/ equivalent of the Romans sense of "right relationship, no damage in the relationship, because that is not in focus here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ginooskoo: know, come to know, perceive;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ginooskoo: know, come to know, perceive; personal intimacy and relationship implied but not asserted. teerein: keep, observe, fulfill, pay attention to<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>entolee: commandment LITERALLY: And by this we know that we know him, if we keep his commandments.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Orang bisa sa omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ada kanál sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt; Ma kalo dia sonde bekin iko Tuhan pung parenta, na, dia tu, tukang putar-balek yang omong laen, bekin laen.<bt>A person can surely (+without thinking) speak saying, &lt;&lt;I know God1.&gt;&gt; But if s/he doesn't do according to God2's command/s, na, s/he is a habitual twister-turner (=idiom; deceiver) who speaks one way, acts another way. [EXEG: the truth is not in him: Msg: his life doesn't match his words (concept "absence of truth" is implicit in 'say one thing, do another' and this is a very well known and natural KM phrase.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who says, &quot;I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who says, "I know him", and does not keep his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang bisa sa bilang, &quot;Beta ini"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Orang bisa sa bilang, "Beta ini orang Sarani; sakarang beta ada jalan pi di sorga, te beta ini Kristus punya." Ma kalu itu orang sonde kasi jalan dia pung idop iko Kristus pung mau, artinya dia itu satu orang tukang putar balek.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ma orang yang bekin iko Tuhan pung parenta, itu jadi bukti bilang, dia pung sayang sang Tuhan su batúl. Deng bagitu, kotong tau bilang, kotong ni, Tuhan pung orang.<bt>But people who do according to God1's command/s, that becomes evidence/proof that his/her love toward God, is already correct/true. In.that.way, we know that, we-inc here, are God2's people. [LEX: "love has been perfected": to try to collocate complete /langkap/ with love /sayang/ results in a big clash. Here the concept of 'complete' is communicated by saying his love for God, is now correct/ideal (implicit: beforehand, it wasn't).]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="DIA"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">DIA</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="an: indefinite condition, &quot;If get one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">an: indefinite condition, "If get one guy..." agape: love<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>alethoos: truly, truly, actually teleiooo: make perfect, perfect, complete<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: But whoever keeps his word, truly the love of God has been perfected in him. By this we know that we are in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Jadi kalo orang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta idop ta'ika deng Tuhan Allah,&gt;&gt; na, dia musti idop sama ke Yesus Kristus.<bt>So (consequently), if a person speaks saying, &lt;&lt;I live bound/linked with God1&gt;&gt;, na, s/he must live like Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="menw: remain, abide, continue opheilw: ought"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">menw: remain, abide, continue opheilw: ought to, must, owe something<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>peripatew: walk, go, go around, live, conduct LITERALLY: The one who says he remains in him ought to live just as that one lived.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ana sayang dong! Parenta yang beta tulis ni, bukan hal baru kasi sang bosong. Te ini parenta su ada memang di Tuhan pung Kata-kata yang bosong su dengar dari dolu.<bt>Beloved children! The command which I write here, is not a new thing for you-pl. Cuz (elaboration) this command has already been previously/beforehand in God2's Words which you have already heard from long ago. [EXEG: what command he is talking about is not explicit in Greek, but it is clear that he assumes this is given/known info to the readers. Commentators agree the rabbinic/Jesus command to Love is the obvious theme. Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agapeetoi: here &quot;good friends&quot; is OK."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">agapeetoi: here "good friends" is OK. LITERALLY: Beloved, I write to you no new commandment, but an old commandment, which you had from the beginning. The old commandment is the word which you heard.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="2:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 13:34</note><v n="8" />Biar bagitu ju, ma ada hal baru yang beta mau tulis so'al Tuhan pung parenta ni. Ini parenta su jalan deng batúl di Yesus pung idop. Deng ini parenta su mulai jalan di bosong, tagal galáp di bosong pung hati su mulai ilang, deng taráng yang batúl su mulai bacaya di bosong pung idop.<bt>Even though it's like that, nevertheless there is a new thing which I want to write about this command of God2's. This command went (=was carried.out) in a correct way/manner in Yesus' life. And this command has begun to be carried.out in you-pl (your lives), because the darkness in your livers has begun to disappear, and the true/correct light has already begun to shine in your lives.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="palin: again alethinos: genuine, real, true|i(8)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">palin: again alethinos: genuine, real, true<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>paragw: pass away, go away, take past skotia: darkness<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>phainw: shine phws: light<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: Yet, I write you a new commandment, which is true in him and in you, because the darkness is going away, and the true light is already shining.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Orang bisa sa ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta idop dalam taráng.&gt;&gt; Ma kalo dia binci dia pung sodara, na, itu jadi tanda bilang, dia masi idop dalam galáp.<bt>A person could speak saying, &lt;&lt;I live in the light.&gt;&gt; But if s/he hates his/her sibling/s, na, that is a sign that, s/he is still living in the dark.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="misew: hate ton adelphon autou: brother"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">misew: hate ton adelphon autou: brother or sister, kin or association (union brothers, people on the same team). [Remark: "Gotta show dis to my cousin!"]<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>arti: now, at the present time, still LITERALLY: The one who says he is in the light, but hates his brother, is in the dark until now.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te orang yang idop dalam taráng, dia musti sayang dia pung sodara, deng sonde ada jahat apa-apa di dia pung hati yang bekin dia jato.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) a person who lives in the light, s/he must love his/her sibling/s, and there is no evil at all in his/her liver which makes him/her fall. [EXEG: TN, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="skandalon: trap, snare, impediment, stumbling block,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">skandalon: trap, snare, impediment, stumbling block, cause to stumble, offend, cause to sin. It doesn't say who is being fouled up, so it could be limited to the brother or sister in question. But it's more like he's not the kind of person who goes around playing games with anyone. LITERALLY: The one who loves his brother remains in the light, and there is no cause to stumble in him.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin orang taantuk ko jato ulang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">bekin orang taantuk ko jato ulang dalam gal�p deng dosa.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Andia ko, kalo ada orang yang binci dia pung sodara, itu jadi tanda bilang, dia ada idop dalam galáp. Dia jalan raba-raba, tagal galáp su bekin buta dia pung mata.<bt>That's why, if there is a person who hates his/her sibling/s, that is a sign that s/he is living in the dark. He/She walks touching-touching (=idiom; groping.to.find.the.way), because the dark has made his/her eyes blind.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupagw: go, go away tuphlow: make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">hupagw: go, go away tuphlow: make blind, to blind<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: But the one who hates his brother is in the dark, and lives in the dark, and does not know where he is going, because the darkness has blinded his eyes.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang idop dalam taráng, sonde idop iko dunya pung mau [\s2]<bt>People who live in the light, do not live following/according to the world's will/desire [NOTE: personification, synecdoche] [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="12" />Ana-ana dong! Beta ada tulis ini surat kasi bosong,<bt>Children! I am writing this letter to you-pl, [EXEG: TH: For I am writing see 2.1.-In vv. 12-13b John uses the present tense of "to write," in vv. 13c and 14 the aorist tense; the latter may be rendered also "I have written" (NEB). This variation is probably a matter of style rather than meaning. KM: uses /ada tulis/ for first set; /tulis/ for second set.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teknia: here may refer to one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">teknia: here may refer to one segment of the group. In 2:1 and 2:18 it's the whole group, and it's possible that that could be the case here; but if it is, why are the three constructions so strongly parallel?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Kristus su mati kasi bosong,<bt>because Kristus has died for you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais Tuhan Allah su hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala dong.<bt>and/so God1 has already wiped/erased away your wrongs,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aphiemi: forgive dia to onoma autou:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">aphiemi: forgive dia to onoma autou: in this context, probably has to do with the fact that you are associated with him (God? Christ?[Ex. Summ leans almost exclusively to Christ]) publicly, committed to be known as his people; his name is bestowed on you. The accusative is "because of," not "through," which would be more like the genitive.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: I write to you little children, because your sins were forgiven through his name [because of him].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="13" />Orang tua dong! Beta ada tulis ini surat kasi bosong,<bt>Old people/parents/clan elders! I am writing this letter to you, [EXEG: See Source, NCV and TranNotes and IVP bible background re ungendered forms of terms. NOTE to daughter translations: Advantage of using /orang tua/ is it pairs nicely with /orang muda/ below; but beware of potential ambiguity. /orang tua/ has two senses 1) parents, 2) clan elders; many people in Kupang default to the second sense; they normally use /mama-bapa/ when they want to specify equiv. of Eng. "parents" CHECK]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal bosong kanál sang Yesus Kristus,<bt>because you-pl know Yesus Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang su ada memang dari dolu-kala.<bt>who already existed beforehand from long ago. [EXEG: Ex. Summ #1]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang muda dong! Beta ada tulis ini surat kasi bosong,<bt>Young people! I am writing this letter to you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal bosong su baparáng lawan jahat pung ba'i,<bt>because you have warred/fought against the grandfather of evil</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">sampe bosong manáng.<bt>to the point that you have won.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="neaniskos: youth, young man nikaw: conquer,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">neaniskos: youth, young man nikaw: conquer, overcome (needs to be parallel with 14)<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>poneros: wicked, evil LITERALLY: I write to you fathers, because you have known the one who is from the beginning. I write to you young men, because you have overcome the Evil One.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="14" />Ana-ana dong! Beta tulis ini surat kasi bosong,<bt>Children! I write this letter to you, [EXEG: See Ex. Summ. on versification. We follow AGNT, NRSV, NLT, CEV and TB. (all the ones we had open), and so never noticed that NIV, KJV, and NASB have a different versification here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal bosong kanál sang Allah Bapa.<bt>because you know Father God.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang tua dong! Beta tulis ini surat kasi bosong,<bt>Old people/parents/clan elders! I write this letter to you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal bosong kanál sang Yesus Kristus,<bt>because you know Yesus Kristus,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang su ada memang dari dolu-kala.<bt>who already existed beforehand from long ago.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Orang muda dong! Beta tulis ini surat kasi bosong,<bt>Young people! I write this letter to you,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal bosong su simpan Tuhan pung Kata-kata dalam bosong pung hati,<bt>because you have stored/put.away God2's Words in your livers,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sampe bosong jadi kuat,<bt>to.the.point. that you have become strong. [EXEG: Marshall]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng bosong su baparáng lawan jahat pung ba'i,<bt>and you have warred/fought with the grandfather of evil,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="grandfather of evil may be seen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">grandfather of evil may be seen as extreme evil, according to Marge ok if not seen as a personality;, same as the world metaphor</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sampe bosong manáng.<bt>to.the.point that you have won.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The verse division of Nestle 26"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">The verse division of Nestle 26 makes a lot more sense than chopping up perfectly good poetry lines like Chinese chicken, RSV style. paidia: child, taken as synonymous with teknia,. It's actually the same word Jesus uses to address his friends in John 21:5, "Hey guys," "Hey pals"<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>isxuros: strong, mighty, powerful, physical strength nenikeekate: needs to be parallel with 13, one way or the other<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: I write to you, children, because you have known the Father. I write to you fathers, because you have known the one who is from the beginning. I write to you young men, because you are strong and the word of God remains in you, and you have overcome the Evil One.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Bosong jang sayang dunya pung mau-mau, deng dunya pung barang. Te orang yang sayang sang dunya, sonde bisa sayang sang Allah Bapa.<bt>You don't love the desires of the world [NOTE: personification], and/nor the things of the world. Cuz (elaboration) a person/people who loves the world, cannot love Father God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ton kosmon: this is the world"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ton kosmon: this is the world as the impermanent place whose inhabitants don't care about God, not the beautiful world of surf and sunsets and people. "Dis world" plugs into the impermanence. The reason for not loving it is not because it's inherently bad, because it isn't; but because it's the place where people do bad things, and it isn't going to be around forever. But the passage itself doesn't really address what characteristics of it we are not supposed to get enamored with. ta en tooi kosmooi: in, not from (contrasts with ek in v. 16)<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: Do not love the world, or the things in the world. If anyone loves the world, love for the Father is not in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Hal yang ada di ini dunya sonde ada pung hubungan deng Tuhan Allah. Conto ke, orang yang idop bekin sanáng dia pung diri sandiri; orang balalas; deng orang yang kapala bésar tagal dia pung kaya. Hal bagitu dong sonde ba'akar di Allah Bapa. Te dong ba'akar di ini dunya sa.<bt>Things which are in this world do not have a connection with God1. For example, a person/people who lives making his/her ownself happy (implicit: not caring about others); greedy person/people; and a person who has a big head (=idiom; proud/arrogant) because of his/her riches. Things like that are not rooted (= do not have origins) in Father God. Cuz (elaboration) they are rooted only in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoti: &quot;You know&quot; helps tie 16"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">hoti: "You know" helps tie 16 and 17 together alazoneia: pretension, pride, insolence, display; ostentation, make tantaran, big show, big noise? inherently looked down on. The other things need an "ony" to make them sound bad because they're selfish.<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>bios: life, means of staying alive, style of living LITERALLY: Because all that is in the world, the lust of the flesh and the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life, is not from the Father, but is from the world.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Padahal ini dunya nanti ilang buang, sama-sama deng itu hal dong yang orang kapingin cari. Ma orang yang kapingin bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, dia sonde ilang buang, te dia nanti idop tarús-tarús.<bt>Whereas in fact, this world will later disappear away, together with those things which people like/desire to seek. But the person who likes/desires to do according to God1's will, s/he will not disappear away, cuz s/he will later live continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the world passes away,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the world passes away, and its lusts, but the one who does the will of God remains forever.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang idop dalam taráng musti ati-ati ko jang kaná tipu [\s2]<bt>People who live in the light must be careful so (they) don't get decieved [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ana-ana dong! Hari-hari kiamat su deka-deka datang. Bosong su dengar bilang, orang yang malawan sang Kristus nanti muncul datang. Padahal dong su ada memang. Te su ada yang malawan sang Kristus di mana-mana. Itu jadi tanda bilang, hari-hari kiamat su deka-deka datang.<bt>Children! The final (end of world) days are already imminently near. You-pl have already heard that people who oppose Kristus will later appear. Whereas in fact they have already appeared (memang=and have been before this). Cuz (elaboration) there already are those who opppose Kristus all over the place. That is a sign that the final days are already imminently near. [EXEG: see Nyland, CEV, Ex. Summ #2; note the Gk has no article, so the idea of The Antichrist (as a single specific person) is based on external assumptions, not textual clues from the Gk in this passage; NOTE to daughter translations: /Kristus pung musu/ or /yang malawan sang Kristus/ is a good match for the Gk. being unmarked for number and not specific.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paidia: by now, &quot;you guys jalike"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">paidia: by now, "you guys jalike my kids" has been beaten to death. Now that he's back to the whole group, we need a more relaxed way of addressing them. And since paidia can be used among adult peers, not just Greek speaking children, let's use a Pidgin phrase appropriate for adult peers. John is keeping his leader-of-the-group stance, in any case. antikhristos: no article; not a name but the characterization of a type<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>LITERALLY: Little children, it is the last hour. And just as you have heard that the Antichrist is coming, even now there are many antichrists. By that we know that it is the last hour.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Tesalonika 2:1-12</note><v n="19" />Itu tukang malawan dong kaluar datang dari kotong pung teng-tenga. Padahal dong tu, bukan kotong pung orang. Te andekata dong batúl-batúl kotong pung orang, na, su tantu dong sonde jalan kasi tenga sang kotong, ma dong batahan tarús sama-sama deng kotong. Ma dong su bangun bongkar. Jadi su jalás, dong tu, bukan kotong pung orang, to?<bt>Those habitual opposers went out/came out from our-inc midst. However/ In.actual.fact, they were not our-inc people. Cuz (elaboration) if perchance [+hypothetical] they really were our people, na, surely they wouldn't go away abandoning us, but they would keep persevering/enduring together with us. But they have got up and cleared out. So (consequently), it's clear, that they were/are not our people, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang lawan = always not going"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">tukang lawan = always not going along with, opposing (opposite of tukang iko =always goes along with) ; vb bamalawan = willfuly and deliberately, actively opposing ; *** Jn &amp; Adr say here should be tukang malawan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: They went out from us,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: They went out from us, but they were not of us. Because if they had been of us, they would have remained with us. But [they went out] so that it might be clear that they were not all of us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma bosong sonde sama deng dong. Te bosong su tarima Tuhan pung Orang Barisi pung Roh. Deng Dia su tolong sang bosong, ko bosong samua mangarti apa yang batúl.<bt>But you-pl are not like them. Cuz (elaboration) you have already received God2's Holy Person's Spirit. And He has already helped you, so that you all understand what is true/correct. [EXEG: Ex. Summ. Annointing: IVP Bible Background: Many commentators hold that the ‘anointing’ (v. 27) is the Spirit (cf. Jn 14:17, 26; Acts 10:38); // Annointing: See Key Biblical Terms 'anoint' for this verse and verse 27. Seems important to not just leave annointing as 'power' kuasa, because that is a cliche and the point here is power to discern spiritual things, not power to boss people around. (could make explicit Holy Spirit gives power to understand) // 'you know (what is true)': TN, NIV, TEV, LB. // TEXT: "you all" vs. "all things" GNT indicates a high degree of doubt. Alf, My, KJV, and NAB. TB, CEV, Source, NLT go for "you all". So do we.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you have an anointing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you have an anointing from the Holy One, and you know all things/all of you have knowledge.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Bosong kira beta tulis ini surat, tagal beta sangka bosong sonde tau apa yang batúl? Sonde! Te bosong su tau na! Bosong su mangarti mana yang batúl, deng mana yang putar-balek.<bt>Do you-pl I write this letter, because I think/assume/guess that you-pl don't know what is true/correct? No! Cuz (elaboration) you already know, of.course! You already understand which (of options) are true/correct, and which are twisted-turned (idiom; deceptive).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouk egrapsa: negative scope is tricky"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ouk egrapsa: negative scope is tricky -- not "I didn't write" but "the reason I did write was not...". Also epistolary aorist. paan pseudos: categorical, not specific lies. But he's leading up to the Big Lie in verse 22. Pinning down lies in general is better accomplished by "Kay den" in 22, not by making 21 more specific than it is.<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>LITERALLY: I have not written to you because you do not know the truth, but because you know it, and because no lie is of the truth.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Padahal ada tukang tipu yang jalan di ini dunya. Karmana ko kotong bisa kanál sang dong? Dong tu, andia orang yang omong bilang, Yesus tu, bukan Kristus. Iko dong, Yesus bukan Orang Barisi yang Tuhan su janji memang ko mau kirim datang. Orang yang omong bagitu, ada bamalawan sang Kristus, te dong tola buang Allah Bapa deng Dia pung Ana.<bt>However, there are habitual deceivers/con artists who walk/operate in this world. How can we know/recognize them? They are people who speak saying, Yesus [+known info], is not Kristus. According to them, Yesus is not the Clean/Holy Person whom God2 already promised beforehand to send. People who speak like that, are (actively, wilfully) opposing Kristus, cuz (elaboration) they reject Father God and His Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arneomai: deny, repudiate, disown someone, reject."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">arneomai: deny, repudiate, disown someone, reject. This is a verbal action, usually rejection of a person, not denial of a proposition, except when used with "hoti" as in the first part of 22. LITERALLY: Who is the liar, except the one who denies that Jesus is the Christ? He is the antichrist, the one who denies the Father and the Son.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Orang yang tola buang sang Tuhan Allah pung Ana, na, dong ju tola buang sang Dia pung Bapa. Ma kalo orang mangaku sang Tuhan Allah pung Ana, na, dong ju su jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana.<bt>People who reject Father God's Child, na, they also reject His Father. But if people acknowledge God1's Child, na, they also have become God1's children. [NOTE to daughter translations: Unlike KM, many vernaculars cannot /mangaku/ s.t. positive in the sense of "affirm, acknowledge" (Jesus Christ as Lord). They can only /mangaku/ "sins". It is a tight collocational restriction. Be sure to check it out carefully, and watch out for the translators wanting to use it just because it is in the Kupang.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arnoumenos ... homologoon: both speech acts;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">arnoumenos ... homologoon: both speech acts; the ensuing actions are not in focus right here. If we tried to work in "say dat Jesus da Spesho Guy God Wen Send" to keep it locked in with 22, it should be "say dat God's Boy, he da Spesho Guy God Wen Send" in order not to violate John's switch of terms. But that begins to sound like a tautology, and misses the fact that John has moved away from a clause with hoti to a plain accusative. LITERALLY: Everyone who denies the Son does not have the Father. The one who confesses the Son has the Father too.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Jadi bosong musti pegang tarús apa yang bosong su dengar dari dolu. Deng bagitu, bosong ta'ika tarús deng Allah Bapa, deng Dia pung Ana.<bt>So (consequently), you-pl must hold on continually to what you have heard from that prior time. In that way, you are bound/linked continually with Father God, and His Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hyiooi ... patri: Putting the Father"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">hyiooi ... patri: Putting the Father first makes for straightforward syntax; putting the Son first leads to a grammatical tangle, because you need to say whose boy. LITERALLY: Let what you have heard from the beginning remain in you. If what you have heard from the beginning remains in you, you will remain in the Son and in the Father too.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Deng Dia sandiri su janji sang kotong bilang, nanti kotong idop tarús-tarús deng Dia.<bt>And He himself has already promised us-inc that later we will live forever with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epaggelia: promise LITERALLY: And this is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">epaggelia: promise LITERALLY: And this is the promise which he promised us, eternal life.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Beta tulis ini surat ko bosong mangarti so'al orang yang mau tipu sang bosong.<bt>I write this letter so that you-pl can/will understand about the people who want to deceive you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I have written these things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I have written these things to you about the ones who deceive you.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Bosong su tarima Tuhan pung Roh Barisi, deng bosong ju su idop ta'ika deng Dia. Jadi bosong sonde parlú orang laen ko ajar sang bosong lai. Te Tuhan pung Roh su cukup, tagal Dia bisa ajar samua hal yang batúl. Dia sonde putar-balek, sama ke itu tukang tipu dong. Jadi pegang kuat-kuat sang apa yang Dia su ajar, ko bosong idop satu hati tarús deng Kristus.<bt>You-pl have already received God2's Clean/Holy Spirit, and you also already live bound/linked with Him. So (consequently), you don't need other people to teach you anymore. Cuz (elaboration) God2's Spirit is already enough/sufficient, because He can teach everything which is true/correct. He doesn't twist-turn (deceive), like those habitual deceivers. So (consequently), hold on strongly to what He has already taught, so that you can continue to live one livered with Kristus. [EXEG: Ex. Summ]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma bosong samua su tarima Roh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Ma bosong samua su tarima Roh Kudus, abis Roh Kudus itu tenga di dalam bosong pung hati. Tagal itu bosong su kanal kebenaran. Kalu bagitu na bosong masi parl� orang laen datang ko ajar tamba kasi bosong apa lai? Roh Kudus sandiri yang su ajar kasi sang bosong bilang Yesus Kristus itu kebenaran. Dia bukan pendusta. Tagal itu, iko apa yang Roh Kudus bilang, bosong musti tat�p idop dalam Kristus.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And the annointing which you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And the annointing which you received from him remains in you, and you do not have need for anyone to teach you. But his annointing teaches you about all things, and is true, and is not a lie. Just as it has taught you, remain in him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Bagini, ana-ana dong! Bosong musti idop ta'ika tarús deng Kristus. Ko biar nanti Dia datang kambali, na, bosong sonde usa taku-taku deng sonde usa malu-malu badiri di Dia pung muka.<bt>It's like this, children! You must live continually bound/linked with Kristus. So that when later He comes back, na, you don't need to be afraid and don't need to be embarrassed/timid to stand in front of Him. [EXEG: KeyT: Key term for 'remain' idop satu hati tarús ~ ta'ika ]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="menete: in the Gospel it's &quot;stay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">menete: in the Gospel it's "stay tight" for menein. But "stick" may include more of an initiative, an "stay tight" a description of the relationship, so "stick" is probably best here. phanerootheei: usually rendered elsewhere as "come back" when it refers to Jesus's second coming<span class="Italic">(28) (28) </span>LITERALLY: And now, little children, remain in him, so that when he appears we may have confidence, and not be ashamed before him at his coming.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Tagal bosong su tau bilang, Dia salalu bekin apa yang batúl, andia ko bosong ju bisa tau bilang, samua orang yang bekin iko apa yang batúl, dong ju jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana.<bt>Because you already know that He always does what is correct/true, that is why you can also know that all people who do according to what is true/correct, they also have become God2's children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: If you know that he"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: If you know that he is righteous, you know that everyone who does what is right has been born from him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana musti idop deng batúl -- Tuhan pung ana-ana sonde idop bekin sala lai [\s2]<bt>People who become/became God1's children must live correctly -- God2's children don't live doing wrong anymore [\s2]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Having Key Term for Devil be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Having Key Term for Devil be a phrasal lexeme (setan dong pung bos) rather than a single word as in English, causes some interesting phrasing and Kupang specific problems in this section</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Coba bosong pikir Bapa di sorga pung sayang sang kotong! Te Dia pung sayang tu, hebat talalu, sampe Dia angka sang kotong jadi Dia pung ana-ana. Itu batúl! Ma orang idop iko dunya pung mau, sonde mangarti kotong ni sapa, tagal dong sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>You-pl try and have a think about Father in heaven2's love for us! Cuz (elaboration) that love of His, is exceedingly amazing/impressive, to the point that He raised/elevated/appointed/adopted us-inc to be/become His children. That's true! But people living according to the desires of the world, don't understand who we-inc are, because they don't know/aren't.acquainted.with God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hina: result, not reason esmen: reality,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">hina: result, not reason esmen: reality, not just a true statement<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: See what kind of love the Father has given us that we should be called children of God; and we are. For this reason the world does not know us, because it did not know him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ana sayang dong! Kotong su jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana, ma balóm jalás nanti kotong mau jadi karmana lai. Yang kotong tau, bagini: nanti kalo Kristus datang kambali, kotong ju jadi sama ke Dia, tagal kotong dapa lia sang Dia taráng-taráng.<bt>Beloved children! We-inc have already become God1's children, but it is not yet clear later how/what else we will become. What we know is like this: later if/when Kristus comes back, we-inc also will become like Him, because we can see Him clearly/openly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Beloved, now we are children"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Beloved, now we are children of God, and it has not been shown what we shall be. We know that when he appears, we will be like him, because we will see him just as he is.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Samua orang yang ada batunggu-tunggu sang Kristus pung datang, tantu dong bekin barisi dong pung idop, ko idop barisi sama ke Kristus.<bt>Everyone who is eagerly-awaiting/anticipating Kristus' coming, surely they will make their lives clean/holy, in order to live clean/holy like Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And everyone who has this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And everyone who has this hope in him purifies himself, just as that one is pure.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Samua sala ada langgar Tuhan pung parenta. Andia ko samua orang yang bekin sala, su langgar Tuhan Allah pung parenta, deng su malawan sang Dia.<bt>All wrong is violating God2's command/s. That's why all people who have done wrong, have violated God1's command/s, and have opposed/resisted/rebelled against Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poioon teen hamartian: generic, not a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">poioon teen hamartian: generic, not a list. No "da" needed. LITERALLY: Everyone who commits sin breaks the law, because sin is breaking the law.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bosong su tau bilang, Kristus jadi manusia ko hapus buang kotong pung sala-sala. Dia bisa bekin bagitu, tagal Dia sandiri sonde parná bekin sala.<bt>You already know that Kristus became human to wipe/erase away our-inc wrongs. He was able to do like that, because He himself had never done wrong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And you know that that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And you know that that one appeared to take away sins, and there is no sin in him.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:29</note><v n="6" />Jadi orang yang idop ta'ika tarús deng Dia, sonde idop bekin sala lai. Ma kalo orang idop bekin sala tarús, dia pung arti bilang, dia sonde kanál deng sonde ta'ika deng Kristus.<bt>So (consequently), people who live bound/linked continually with Him, don't live doing wrong anymore. But if a.person lives doing wrong continually, it's means that s/he doesn't know/be.acquainted.with and isn't bound/linked with Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Everyone who remains in him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Everyone who remains in him does not continue to sin. Everyone who continues to sin has not seen him or known him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ana sayang dong! Jang kaná tipu. Te orang yang idop bekin iko apa yang batúl, dia tu, orang hati lurus, sama ke Kristus.<bt>Beloved children! Don't be deceived. Cuz (elaboration) the person who lives doing according to what is true/correct, s/he is a straight livered (righteous/just) person, like Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teknia: as if they were his"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">teknia: as if they were his own children ho poioon teen dikaiosyneen dikaios estin: if dikaios is mainly focused on correct behavior in this letter, which it probably is, then we have to work around a tautology in Pidgin.<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: Children, do not let anyone deceive you. The one who does righteousness/justice is righteous/just, just as he is righteous/just.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma orang yang idop bekin sala, dia ba'akar di setan jahat dong pung bos. Te dia yang maen bekin jahat dari mula-mula. Andia ko Tuhan pung Ana datang ko kasi ancor itu setan pung bekin jahat.<bt>But a person who lives doing wrong, he is rooted.in (linked to source) the evil spirit's boss. Cuz (elaboration) he is the one who repeatedly did evil from the very beginning. That's why God2's Child came to destroy the evil doings of that evil spirit (=Devil). [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK if last "evil spirit" actually tracks to evil spirit's boss for the UNS's.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poioon: generic, �keeps on practicing (sin)�"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">poioon: generic, �keeps on practicing (sin)� lyseei ta erga tou diabolou: in general, not specifically in the life of one person, though it starts there<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>LITERALLY: The one who sins is of the Devil, because from the beginning the Devil has sinned. For this the Son of God appeared, to destroy the works of the Devil.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Orang yang su jadi Tuhan pung ana sonde idop bekin sala lai, tagal Tuhan ada idop di dia pung diri. Dia sonde bisa bekin sala tarús, tagal dia ba'akar di Tuhan.<bt>A person who has already become God2's child doesn't live doing wrong anymore, because God2 is living in his/her self. He/She cannot do wrong continually, because s/he is rooted in God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Everyone who has been born"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Everyone who has been born from God does not continue to sin, because his seed remains in him, and he cannot sin, because he has been born from God.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Deng bagitu, kotong bisa tau sapa yang ba'akar di Tuhan Allah, deng sapa yang ba'akar di setan dong pung bos. Te orang yang sonde bekin iko apa yang batúl, deng orang yang sonde tau sayang sang dia pung sodara, itu jadi tanda bilang, dia sonde ba'akar di Tuhan Allah.<bt>In that.way, we-inc can know who is rooted in God1, and who is rooted in the evil spirits' boss. Cuz (elaboration) a person who doesn't do according to what is correct/true, and a person who doesn't know (=doesn't want to) love his/her sibling, that is a sign that s/he is not rooted in God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="righteous key term: idop iko apa/jalan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">righteous key term: idop iko apa/jalan yg batul; orang hati lurus</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By this is shown the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By this is shown the difference between the children of God and the Children of the Devil: Everyone who does not do righteousness is not from God, nor the one who does not love his brother.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana musti basayang satu deng satu [\s2]<bt>God1's children must love each other [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Dari dolu-dolu, bosong su dengar memang ini pasán yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Basayang satu deng satu!&gt;&gt;<bt>From long ago you-pl have already heard (before this) this (+known) message which says, &lt;&lt;Love each other!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anggelia: i.e. the message brought by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">anggelia: i.e. the message brought by an /anggelos/ �messenger� LITERALLY: Because this is the message which you heard from the beginning, that we should love each other.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 13:34</note><v n="12" />Masi inga Kaen deng Habel pung carita, to? Naa, jang bekin iko Kaen, te dia ba'akar di jahat pung ba'i, sampe dia bunu bekin mati dia pung adi Habel. Akurang ko dia bekin bagitu? Itu tagal dia bekin hal-hal yang jahat, ma dia pung adi bekin hal-hal yang batúl.<bt>You still remember Kaen and Habel's story, right? Naa, don't do like Kaen, cuz (elaboration) he was rooted in the grandfather of evil to the point that he murdered killed his younger sibling Habel. Why did he do like that? That was because he did things which were evil, but his younger sibling did things which were correct/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="poneera: generic; Gk is not /diabolos/"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">poneera: generic; Gk is not /diabolos/ but /poneiros/ �the evil one� here; most commentators feel John is deliberate in using a different term here dikaia: also generic, but "da" is part of a set phrase here.<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: Not like Cain who was from the Evil One and murdered his brother. And for what did he murder him? Because his deeds were evil, but his brother's were righteous.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 4:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Sodara dong! Jang heran kalo orang yang iko dunya pung mau-mau binci sang bosong.<bt>Siblings! Don't be surprised/amazed if/when people who follow the world's desires hate you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ei: factual -- they're going to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ei: factual -- they're going to hate you anyway LITERALLY: And do not be surprised, brothers, if the world hate you.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Kotong su tau bilang, kalo orang sala nanti mati, na, dia tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah. Ma tagal kotong basayang deng kotong pung sodara, itu jadi bukti bilang, kalo kotong nanti mati, na, kotong idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan. Te kalo samua orang yang sonde ada pung sayang nanti mati, na, dong tapisa buang dari Tuhan.<bt>We-inc know if/when a wrong person later dies, and s/he is separated away from God1. But because we-inc love our sibling/s, that shows proof that, if/when we later die, we will live forever with God2. Cuz (elaboration) if/when all people who have no love later die, they will be separated apart from God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Secondary use of die; here; good"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Secondary use of die; here; good verse for PL</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dead as &quot;no longer among the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">Dead as "no longer among the living" probably needs to be translated differently from dead as "subject to eternal damnation". "Cut off from God" seems to fit most contexts. LITERALLY: We know that he have passed out of death into life, because we love the brothers. The one who does not love remains in death.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalu kotong sayang satu deng satu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Kalu kotong sayang satu deng satu, kotong kasi tunju trang-trang bilang kotong su talapas dari naraka, deng kotong su dapa idop yang kekal. Ma orang yang sonde sayang orang laen, dong kasi lia bilang dong ada jalan maso pi dalam kematian yang kekal.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 5:24</note><v n="15" />Te orang yang binci dia pung sodara, dia ju sama ke orang yang bunu bekin mati orang. Naa, bosong su tau bilang, orang macam bagitu sonde dapa idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who hates his/her sibling, s/he is also like a person who murders people/person. Naa, you already know that people/person like that do not obtain eternal life with God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anthroopoktonos: predicate position paas anthroopoktonos: murderers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">anthroopoktonos: predicate position paas anthroopoktonos: murderers in general.<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: Everyone who hates his brother is a murderer, and you know that no murderer has eternal life remaining in him.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Kotong bisa kanál sayang yang batúl dari Kristus pung conto. Te Dia sayang sang kotong, sampe Dia sarakan Dia pung diri deng mati, ko ganti sang kotong. Tagal itu, kotong ju musti sadia sarakan kotong pung idop kasi sang kotong pung sodara dong.<bt>We-inc can know/recognize correct/true love from Kristus' example. Cuz (elaboration) He loved us, to the point that He handed over His self and died, in order to replace/substitute for us. Because of that, we also must be prepared to hand over our lives for our siblings.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egnookamen: have come to know love"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">egnookamen: have come to know love LITERALLY: By this we know love, because that one laid down his life for us, and we ought to lay down our lives for the brothers.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Kalo ada orang yang idop cukup, ais dia dapa lia satu sodara yang idop susa, ma dia pung hati sonde jato kasian ko tolong sang dia, karmana ko itu orang bisa omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sayang sang Tuhan Allah!&gt;&gt; Sonde bisa!<bt>If there is a person who lives sufficiently (=not in poverty), then s/he gets/happens to a see a sibling who is living in difficulty, but his/her liver doesn't have pity to help him/her, how can that person be able to speak saying, &lt;&lt;I love God1!&gt;&gt; [He/she] can't!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But whoever has the world's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But whoever has the world's possessions, and sees his brother in need, and closes his heart against him, how does the love of God remain in him?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ana sayang dong! Jang cuma sayang deng omong manis pake kata-kata sa, ma bekin hal bae ju, ko kasi tunju sayang yang batúl.<bt>Beloved children! Don't just love by just speaking sweetly using words, but also do good things, to show love which is true/correct.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meeagapoomen: exhortation, but a generic or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">meeagapoomen: exhortation, but a generic or impersonal presentation is more congenial in Pidgin for enunciating a principle. Take out the "we"s LITERALLY: Children, let us not love in word nor speech but in deed and truth.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Te kalo kotong kasi tunju sayang deng bekin hal bae bagitu, kotong bisa tau bilang, kotong ada idop iko yang batúl. Deng bagitu, kotong sonde usa taku-taku, deng kotong bisa angka muka waktu kotong mangada sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Cuz if we-inc show love and do good things like that, we can know that we are living according to what is true/correct. In.that.way, we don't need to afraid, and we can lift our faces (justifiable pride) when we face/report/front up from summons to God1. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emprosthen autou: in God's view of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">emprosthen autou: in God's view of us? when we come before him in prayer? The latter is narrower than "emprosthen" usually is, though it might lead neatly into 21-22. LITERALLY: And in this we know that we are of the truth, and reassure our hearts before him.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Biar kotong pung hati masi maen tudu sang kotong so'al hal sonde bae yang kotong parná bekin, na, kotong sonde usa taku-taku. Te Tuhan Allah pung rasa kasian lebe dari kotong pung. Deng Dia ju tau samua-samua.<bt>Even though our-inc livers still repeatedly accuse us about things that are not good which we have ever done, na, we don't need to be afraid/fearful. Cuz (elaboration) God1's feeling of pity/mercy is much more than ours. And He also knows everything. [EXEG: See Ex. Summ. for complexities of ‘greater than’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kataginooskei: this continues v. 19. We"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">kataginooskei: this continues v. 19. We really are OK with God, but thinking about our past sins ties us in knots. Knowing that we really are God's people is a major theme in 1 John. LITERALLY: Because whenever our hearts condemn us, God is greater than our hearts, and he knows everything.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ana sayang dong! Kalo kotong pung hati sonde tudu sang kotong, na, kotong bisa parcaya diri deng sonde usa malu waktu kotong datang mangada sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Beloved children! If our-inc livers don't accuse us, na, we can have confidence in ourselves and don't need to be timid/embarressed, when we come face/report/front up from summons to God1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parreesian: confidence, not righteousness pros: not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">parreesian: confidence, not righteousness pros: not quite "emprosthen"; you have "parreesian pros" somebody you have a relationship of confidence with. So even if "emprosthen" in 19 comes through as "when we pray" (it could as easily be "when we are called on the carpet"), it's not certain that "pros" is in the same relation to "parreesian" as "emprosthen" is to "peithoo". On the other hand, John could have switched terms just to keep from boring his readers; they're certainly in the same ball park, and "pros" leads to "aitoomen" in the next verse.<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>The sentence kind of rolls along, and it's hard to chop it into typically short Pidgin sentences because then a bunch of connectors have to be fitted and the continuity gets jerky. Pidgin occasionally does this, but it's rare. LITERALLY: Beloved, whenever our heart does not condemn us, we have confidence before God.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Tagal kotong bekin iko Dia pung parenta dong, deng bekin sanáng Dia pung hati, andia ko kotong bisa tarima samua hal yang kotong minta dari Dia.<bt>Because we-inc do according to His commands, and make His liver happy, that's why we can receive all things which we request from Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And whatever we ask we"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And whatever we ask we receive from him, because we keep his commands, and do what is pleasing before him.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Dia pung parenta bilang bagini: parcaya tarús sang Dia pung Ana Yesus Kristus, yang Dia su kirim datang. Deng sayang tarús satu deng satu, sama ke yang Yesus su parenta tu.<bt>His command/s, say is like this: continually believe in His Child Yesus Kristus, whom He has sent. And continually love each other, like what Yesus commanded (+you already know it). [EXEG: just as he: "he" = Yesus. Ex. Summ #1]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And this is his command:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And this is his command: that we believe in the name of his Son Jesus Christ and love each other, just as he gave us a command.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 13:34, 15:12, 17</note><v n="24" />Orang yang bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta dong, dia idop ta'ika deng Tuhan Allah. Deng Tuhan ju ada ta'ika deng dia. Kotong tau Dia ada di kotong pung hati, tagal Dia pung Roh ada idop di situ.<bt>A.person who does according to God1's commands, s/he lives bound/linked with God1. And God2 is also bound/linked with him/her. We-inc know He is in our livers, because His Spirit is living there. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Everyone who keeps his commands"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Everyone who keeps his commands remains in him and he in him. By this we know that he remains in us, by the Spirit he has given us.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana musti ati-ati ko dong jang kaná tipu [\s2]<bt>God1's children must be careful so they are not deceived [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Ana sayang dong! Jang tarima bodo-bodo sa, kalo orang bilang dia ada bawa pasán dari Tuhan Allah. Ma bosong musti pareksa bae-bae ko dapa tau kalo dia pung omong tu, batúl-batúl datang dari Tuhan, ko sonde. Te sakarang su banya tukang putar-balek yang jalan kuliling di ini dunya. Dong tipu orang bilang, dong tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir.<bt>Beloved children! Don't just accept/agree stupidly (=accept 'blindly', without thinking), if a person says s/he is bringing a message from God1. But you-pl must carefully examine it to find out if what s/he is saying, is truly coming from God2, or not. Cuz (elaboration) now there are already many habitual twister-turners (=deceivers) who walk (=do their work) all around this world. They deceive people saying, they are God1's spokesperson. [EXEG: /pneumati/: "spirits" as used here is not neccessarily a cosmological being (and it would be difficult to say which one); CEV, TN, TH, "spirit of man." the seat or source of man's insight, feeling, and will. Ex.Summ.#3.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Beloved, do not trust every"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Beloved, do not trust every spirit, but test the spirits to see if they are from God, because many false prophets have gone out into the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Kotong bisa kanál pasán yang batúl-batúl datang dari Tuhan pung Roh, bagini: Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang Dia pung Ana di ini dunya. Kalo itu orang yang bawa pasán mangaku bilang, Yesus Kristus tu, batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana yang jadi manusia sama ke kotong, na, dia pung pasán tu, memang datang dari Tuhan.<bt>We-inc can know/recognize messages which truly come from God2's Spirit, like this: God1 already promised beforehand long ago to send His Child to this world. If that person who brings a message confesses/acknowledges that Yesus Kristus [+known ref] is truly God1's Child who became human like us-inc, na, that message of his/hers, truly comes from God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By this you know the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By this you know the Spirit of God: every spirit that confesses that Jesus Christ came in the flesh is from God,</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma orang yang sonde mangaku sang Yesus bagitu, dia sonde ba'akar di Tuhan Allah. Te itu datang dari yang bamalawan sang Kristus. Bosong su parná dengar bilang, yang bamalawan sang Kristus tu, nanti muncul datang. Padahal, yang bagitu su ada memang di ini dunya.<bt>But a person who doesn't acknowledge Yesus like that, s/he isn't rooted in God1. Cuz (elaboration) that comes from the one who/those who/that which oppose/s Kristus. You have already heard that, that [+known] one who/those who/that which oppose/s Kristus, will later appear. In actual fact, one/s like that are already present in this world. [EXEG: "spirit of antichrist" unmarked for number in KM, and unmarked for specificity in both Gk and KM; Nyland, The Source; many commentators gloss this without (the) before antichrist here to indicate its broad scope in the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and every spirit that does"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and every spirit that does not confess Jesus is not from God. This is the spirit of (the) antichrist, whom you have heard that he/it is coming, and now he/it is already in the world.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ana sayang dong! Bosong tu, memang ba'akar di Tuhan Allah, deng Dia pung kuasa ada di bosong pung hati. Andia ko bosong su kasi kala sang dong yang bamalawan sang Tuhan. Te Dia pung Roh yang ada di bosong pung hati, lebe hebat dari kuasa yang ada di ini dunya.<bt>Beloved children! You-pl there, really are rooted in God1, and His power is in your livers. That's why you have defeated those who oppose God2. Cuz (elaboration: grounds) His Spirit that is in your livers, is more impressive/amazing than the power that is in this world. [EXEG: purposefully leaving unspecified who the he is, that is in the world. Msg, TH, TN, this is talking about power in this verse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: You are from God, little"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: You are from God, little children, and you have defeated them, because he who is in you is greater than he who is in the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Dong tu, ba'akar di ini dunya. Andia ko dong pung omong ju ba'akar di ini dunya pung mau-mau. Ais orang di ini dunya suka dengar sang dong.<bt>[As for them] they are rooted in this world. That's why what they say is also rooted in the desires of this world. So/Thus people in this world like to hear them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="autoi: the only antecedent available is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">autoi: the only antecedent available is "spirits". V. 6 is still talking about spirits. LITERALLY: They are from the world. Because of this what they say is from the world and the world listens to them.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma kotong ba'akar di Tuhan. Andia ko orang yang kanál sang Tuhan mau dengar sang kotong. Ma orang yang sonde ba'akar di Tuhan, dong sonde mau dengar sang kotong. Deng bagitu, kalo orang bilang dia ada bawa pasán dari Tuhan, kotong bisa tau mana yang batúl, yang ba'akar di Tuhan pung Roh, deng mana yang putar-balek.<bt>But we-inc are rooted in God2. That's why people who know God2 want to listen to us. But people who are not rooted in God2, they don't want to listen to us. In that.way, if a person says s/he is bringing a message from God2, we can know which (of options) is correct/true, that is rooted in God2's Spirit, and which is twisted-turned (=deceptive/false). [DISCOURSE: explication for high-level cohesion.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We are from God. The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We are from God. The one who knows God listens to us. The one who is not from God does not listen to us. By this we know the Spirit of truth and the spirit of lying.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sayang deng Parcaya -- Sayang tu, apa? [\s2]<bt>Love and Faith -- What is Love? [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ana sayang dong! Kotong musti basayang satu deng satu, tagal sayang tu, ba'akar di Tuhan Allah. Samua orang yang basayang, dong ju ba'akar di Tuhan Allah, deng kanál bae sang Dia.<bt>Beloved children! We-inc must love each other, because love [+that we have been talking about], is rooted in God1. All people who love, they also are rooted in God1, and know Him well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nestle 26 sets this whole passage"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">Nestle 26 sets this whole passage as poetry. The first quatrain scans pretty well, but the rest is kind of helter-skelter, and some translations set it as if it were not conscious verse. LITERALLY: Beloved, let us love each other, because love is from God, and everyone who loves has come from God and knows God.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma orang yang sonde ada pung sayang, dia sonde kanál sang Tuhan. Tagal Tuhan tu, andia sayang.<bt>But a.person who does not have love, s/he does not know God. Because God [+known ref], is love.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="te Tuhan Allah itu kasi sayang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">te Tuhan Allah itu kasi sayang pung pohon.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde mungkin kanal eg. Logic: Message"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">sonde mungkin kanal eg. Logic: Message you "can't know God if you don't love." Sonde mungkin kanal sang Tuhan: because it's not simply don't love and don't know God, but can't know God if don't love. Last sent: see Msg: God is love -- you can't know him if you don't love.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who does not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who does not love does not know God, because God is love.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung sayang sang kotong bagini: Dia kirim Dia pung Ana satu biji datang dalam ini dunya, ko buka jalan kasi kotong. Deng bagitu, kotong bisa idop tarús-tarús deng Tuhan.<bt>God2 shows/ed His love to us-inc like this: He sent His one-and-only (lit: one seed) Child to come to this world, to open the way for us. In that way, we can live forever with God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By this the love of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By this the love of God is demonstrated among us, because God sent his one and only Son into the world that we might live through him.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Kalo mau lia sayang yang batúl, jang lia kotong pung sayang sang Tuhan. Ma lia Tuhan pung sayang sang kotong, tagal Dia kirim Dia pung Ana ko mati jadi korban ganti sang kotong. Deng bagitu, Dia hapus buang kotong pung sala dong, ko kotong bisa babae kambali deng Dia.<bt>If [you] want to see real/true love, don't look at our-inc love for God2. But look at God2's love for us, because He sent His Child to die become a sacrifice to replace us. With that He erased away our wrongs, so that we can be in a reciprocally.good.relationship again with Him [NOTE: in a reciprocally good relationship: explicating result of sacrifice as in the Message. "again" is simply implying a former state with a reconciled relationship.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: This is what love is,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: This is what love is, not that we loved God, but that he loved us, and sent his Son as a substitute sacrifice for our sins.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ana sayang dong! Tagal Tuhan Allah su sayang talalu sang kotong bagitu, na, kotong ju musti basayang satu deng satu.<bt>Beloved children! Because God1 has loved us exceedingly like that, na, we also must love each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Beloved, since God loved us"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Beloved, since God loved us like that, we also ought to love each other.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Sonde ada satu orang ju yang parná lia taráng-taráng sang Tuhan Allah. Biar bagitu ju, ma kalo kotong basayang satu deng satu, dia pung arti bilang, Tuhan Allah ada sama-sama deng kotong. Deng Dia pung sayang batamba di kotong pung idop, sampe jadi sayang yang batúl.<bt>There is not a single person who ever has seen God1 clearly. Even though it's like that, nevertheless if we love each other, it means God1 is together with us. And His love increases in our lives, until becoming love which is correct/real/ fits.the.ideal.concept.of.something. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung sayang makin lama makin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Dia pung sayang makin lama makin b�sar di dalam kotong pung diri.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tetheatai: has had a good look"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">tetheatai: has had a good look at God (in Genesis several people saw him in disguise, and in Exodus he says he allowed himself to be seen). LITERALLY: No one has ever seen God. If we love each other, God stays among us, and his love is made perfect among us.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 1:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Tuhan Allah su kasi Dia pung Roh di kotong pung hati. Andia ko kotong tau bilang, kotong idop satu hati deng Dia, deng Dia ju satu hati deng kotong.<bt>God1 has given/put His Spirit in our-inc livers. That's why we know that, we live one livered (idiom: in.unity/harmony/accord) with Him, and He also is one livered with us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en toutooi: cataphoric &quot;dis&quot; refers to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">en toutooi: cataphoric "dis" refers to something not filled in yet. "Dat" or "Dass" would be anaphoric, pointing back to verse 12. menomen: "stay tight" is a little more stative, "stick wit" a little more active. Here it's talking about the relationship that exists, not about our action in taking it, so it's stative.<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>TERM: Though the idea of a spirit being "inside" somebody is not impossible, the usual way of talking about the phenomenon is with "take ova" or "stay in charge a". The inverse is "let um go". In lexical function terms, the locus of "take ova" where spirits are concerned is "inside", but "take ova" is the primary lexeme. LITERALLY: By this we know that we remain in him and he in us, because he has given us his Spirit.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Beta, deng beta pung tamán dong su dapa lia Tuhan Allah pung Ana deng botong pung mata kapala sandiri. Ais botong kasi tau samua orang bilang, Allah Bapa su kirim datang Dia pung Ana, ko kasi salamat orang di ini dunya dari dong pung sala-sala.<bt>Me, and my friends have seen God1's Child with our very own eyes. Thus we tell all people saying, Father God has sent His Child, to save the people in this world from their wrongs/sins.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And we have seen and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And we have seen and testify that the Father sent his Son as Savior of the world.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Samua orang yang mangaku bilang, Yesus tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana, dia idop babae deng Tuhan Allah, deng Tuhan ju babae deng dia.<bt>All people who acknowledge that, Yesus [+known ref], is God1's Child, s/he lives in a reciprocally good relationship with God1, and God2 also is reciprocally good with him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Whoever confesses that Jesus is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Whoever confesses that Jesus is the Son of God, God remains in him and he in God.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Kotong su tau bilang, Tuhan sayang talalu sang kotong. Andia ko kotong parcaya bilang, nanti Dia ju sayang tarús sang kotong.<bt>We already know that God2 loves us exceedingly. That's why we believe that later He will also continue to love us. [EXEG: NLT &amp; others translations also put paragraph break in this verse. TN: "Also we-inc know well that God loves us, and we trust him to love us all the time."]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tuhan sayang talalu sang orang. Jadi orang yang ada idop basayang, ju ada idop satu hati deng Tuhan Allah, deng Tuhan satu hati deng dia ju.<bt>God loves people to the max. So the person who is living in reciprocal love (with others), also is living one livered with God1, and God2 also one livered with him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="1 Cor 13"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">1 Cor 13</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kai ... Ho theos agapee estin:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">kai ... Ho theos agapee estin: the connective at verse 16 and the asyndeton at 16b make Nestle's paragraphing attractive. LITERALLY: And we know and have believed the love which God has for us. God is love, and the one who remains in love remains in God and God remains in him.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Deng kalo kotong satu hati deng Tuhan, na, kotong pung sayang jadi batúl. Ais nanti kalo hari kiamat, Tuhan mau pareksa samua orang pung idop, na, kotong sonde usa taku-taku badiri di Dia pung muka, tagal kotong su jadi sama ke Kristus waktu Dia idop di ini dunya.<bt>And, if/when we-inc are one livered with God2, na, our love becomes love which is true/correct/fits.the.ideal.concept. So then later if/when it is the final day (=end of world), God2 wants to examine all pe.ople's lives, na, we don't need to be afraid/be fearful to stand in front of Him, because we have become like/the same as Kristus when He lived on this earth. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en toutooi teteleiootai: this is what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">en toutooi teteleiootai: this is what it takes to make it complete heemoon: probably inclusive here: "all us guys"<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>hina: result, not purpose LITERALLY: By this love has been made perfect with us, that we have confidence on the day of judgment, because just as that one is, we also are in this world.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng, kalo kotong pung sayang su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Deng, kalo kotong pung sayang su jadi sayang yang bat�l, nanti kalo hari kiamat, Tuhan mau pareksa samua orang pung idop, na, kotong sonde usa taku-taku badiri di Dia pung muka, tagal kotong su jadi sama ke Kristus waktu Dia idop di ini dunya.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Kalo kotong idop deng basayang, na, kotong sonde ada pung rasa taku sadiki ju. Te kalo kotong sayang deng batúl, na, itu sama ke kotong su angka buang kaluar samua rasa taku di kotong pung hati. Kalo orang taku, dia pung hati susa, tagal dia taku kaná hukum. Dia sama ke ana kici yang balóm tau sayang orang deng batúl.<bt>If we-inc live and/by loving each other, na, we don't have even a tiny bit of fear. Cuz (elaboration) if we love in a true/real/ideal manner, na, that is the same as if we have picked up throwed out all the feeling of fear in our livers. If a person is afraid, his/her liver is distressed/troubled, because s/he is afraid of being punished. He/She is like a small child who does not yet know how to love people in a true/ideal manner.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="3rd singular impersonal, usually subjectless in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">3rd singular impersonal, usually subjectless in Pidgin, as statement of a principle. Also negative subjects don't communicate. kolasin: punishment<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>ou teteleiootai: "not grown up" by itself may get close to "sexually immature" rather than "has a ways to go before he has really developed a loving attitude" LITERALLY: There is no fear in love, but perfect love throws out fear, because fear has to do with punishment, but the one who fears has not been made mature by love.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Kotong sayang, tagal Tuhan Allah sayang lebe dolo sang kotong.<bt>We-inc love, because God1 loved us first.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We love, because he loved"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We love, because he loved us first.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagal kotong su rasa lebe dolo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">tagal kotong su rasa lebe dolo TA pung sayang sang kotong.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Kalo orang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sayang sang Tuhan Allah,&gt;&gt; padahal dia binci sang dia pung sodara, dia tu, omong kosong sa. Te kalo orang sonde sayang dia pung sodara yang ada di dia pung muka idong, na, karmana ko dia bisa sayang sang Tuhan Allah yang dia balóm parná lia? Sonde mungkin, to?<bt>If a person speaks saying, &lt;&lt;I love God1,&gt;&gt; whereas in fact he hates his sibling, that person is just speaking emptily (=lying). Cuz (elaboration) if a person doesn't love his/her sibling who is right in front of his nose-face, na, how can s/he love God1 whom s/he has not yet ever seen? Impossible, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adelphon: generic for a fellow Christian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">adelphon: generic for a fellow Christian of either sex LITERALLY: If someone says that he loves God, and hates his brother, he is a liar. Because the one who does not love his brother whom he has seen, cannot love God whom he has not seen.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Te Tuhan Allah sandiri su kasi turun parenta bilang, kotong jang cuma sayang sang Dia sa, ma kotong ju musti sayang sang kotong pung sodara orang parcaya dong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God1 himself has sent down the command saying, we-inc mustn't just love only Him, but we must also love our fellow believers. [EXEG: NRSV, NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And this is the command"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And this is the command we have from him, that the one who loves God should love his brother too.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Samua orang yang parcaya bilang, Yesus tu, memang Kristus yang Tuhan Allah su kirim datang, dong tu, su jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana-ana. Te orang yang sayang satu orang yang jadi bapa, dia ju sayang sang itu bapa pung ana.<bt>All people who believe that Yesus [+known ref], is truly Kristus, whom God1 sent, [as for them] they have already become God1's children. Cuz (elaboration), people who love a person who is a father, s/he also loves that father's children. [EXEG: The Gk is ‘the one having given birth’ and ‘the one having been born’, so it is a broader principle than just God the Father and Jesus the Son; it also introduces v.2. NRSV: and everyone who loves the parent loves the child. Also heavy support in Ex.Summ. KM in this context works better with gendered "father" than with ungendered "parent". CONNECTOR: Gk. /kai/ can have a sense of "and furthermore" = elaboration, so KM te.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***Te orang yang sayang sang orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">***Te orang yang sayang sang orang tua, dia ju sayang sang itu orang tua pung ana. ; Te orang yang sayang satu orang yang jadi bapa, dia ju sayang sang itu bapa pung ana.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Everyone who believes that Jesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Everyone who believes that Jesus is the Christ has been born from God, and everyone who loves the father loves his child too.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Kalo kotong sayang sang Tuhan, deng bekin iko Dia pung parenta, itu kasi tunju bilang, kotong ju sayang sang Dia pung ana-ana dong.<bt>If we love God2 and do according to His command/s, that shows/demonstrates that we also love his His children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: By this we know that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God and keep his commands.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Jadi kalo kotong sayang sang Dia, kotong bekin iko Dia pung parenta dong. Deng Dia pung parenta, sonde barát.<bt>So (consequently), if we love Him, we do according to His commands. And His commands are not heavy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bareiai: heavy, burdensome, load us down."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">bareiai: heavy, burdensome, load us down. It may be hard, but it's not crushing. LITERALLY: For this is the love of God, that we keep his commands; and his commands are not burdensome.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 14:15</note><v n="4" />Kotong yang su jadi Tuhan pung ana-ana, bisa manáng lawan dunya pung mau-mau, tagal kotong parcaya sang Dia.<bt>We who have become God2's children, can win over the desires of the world, because we believe in Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hee pistis heemoon: &quot;trus somebody&quot; LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">hee pistis heemoon: "trus somebody" LITERALLY: because everyone who is born from God overcomes the world; and this is the victory which overcomes the world: our faith.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Te orang yang bisa kasi kala dunya pung mau-mau, andia orang yang parcaya bilang, Yesus tu, Tuhan Allah pung Ana.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the person who can defeat the desires of the world, is the person who believes that Yesus [+known ref], is God1's Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Generic needs to be expressed by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">Generic needs to be expressed by the singular here because of "ony." ho pisteuoon hoti: "trus" is probably not the best rendering. "Stay shua"<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: Who is the one who overcomes the world? Only the one who believes that Jesus is the Son of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Parcaya sang Yesus, dia pung guna apa? [\s2]<bt>Believing in Yesus, what is it useful for? [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Asal bosong tau: Yesus tu, bukan cuma manusia biasa sa. Te Dia ju Kristus yang Tuhan Allah su kirim datang di ini dunya. Waktu Dia su mau kasi jalan Dia pung karjá, Yohanis sarani sang Dia pake aer. Ais itu, Dia ju mati deng tumpa Dia pung dara. Jadi yang pantíng, bukan cuma aer yang Yohanis pake ko sarani sang Dia, ma Dia pung dara yang tumpa, pantíng ju. Te Tuhan Allah pung Roh sandiri yang kasi tau bagitu, deng Dia sonde tau putar-balek.<bt>Just so you know. Yesus [+known ref], was not just an ordinary human. Cuz (elaboration) He is also Kristus whom God1 has sent to this world. When He was about to carry out His work, Yohanis baptised Him using water. After that, He also died and/by spilling out His blood. So (consequently) what is important, is not just the water which Yohanis used to baptise Him, but His blood which spilt out, is also important. Cuz (elaboration) God1's Spirit himself is the who tells like that, and He does not twist-turn (=deceive). [EXEG: TH, TN, Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en: not &quot;because John baptized him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">en: not "because John baptized him ... because they killed him" but "referring to the occasion when" LITERALLY: This is the one who comes by water and blood, Jesus Christ. Not by water only, but by water and blood. And the Spirit is the witness, because the Spirit is true.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kotong tau, bilang, Yesus itu Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Kotong tau, bilang, Yesus itu Tuhan Allah pung Ana, sebab Tuhan Allah sandiri yang kasi suara bagitu dari langit waktu Yesus sarani abis satu kali lai waktu deka-deka deng Yesus pung mati. Jadi itu suara ini bukan cuma dapa dengar waktu sarani sang Dia, ma juga waktu Dia su mangada deka-deka deng Dia pung mati. De Roh Kudus, yang salalu bat�l, ju omong, bilang, bagitu. Jadi kotong ada tiga saksi: Roh Kudus pung suara di dalam kotong pung hati, suara dari langit waktu sarani sang Tuhan Yesus, deng suara yang datang lebe dolu dari Dia pung mati. Ini tiga saksi ini yang omong ini hal, bilang, Yesus Kristus itu Tuhan Allah pung Ana.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Te ada tiga hal yang jadi saksi:<bt>So (consequently), there are three things which are witnesses: [EXEG on ftn: TNIV (for date on appearing in translations), NRSV, NLT; but Carson (1979) has it showing up in one or two hand-written margin notes after A.D. 800.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) Jadi changed to te,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">*** (2009) Jadi changed to te, to better reflect Gk here.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada Alkitab laen yang tulis tamba bilang, [&lt;&lt;(7b) di sorga, andia Bapa, Kata-kata, deng Roh Barisi. (8a) Deng ini tiga dong tu, satu. Deng ada tiga hal yang jadi saksi di bumi,&gt;&gt;]. Padahal ini kata dong sonde ada dalam tulisan <span class="Italic">bahasa Yunani asli</span> dong. Dong muncul tamba dalam satu-dua Alkitab laen mulai dari abad ka-14.<bt>There are other Bibles that add saying, [“(7b) in heaven, that is the Father, the Words/Sayings, and the Holy Spirit. (8a) And the three of these are one. And there are three things which are witnesses on earth,”]. Whereas in fact, these words do not exist in the original Yunani language writings. They appear additionally in one or two other Bibles beginning from the 14th century.</bt></note><v n="8" />andia, Tuhan pung Roh, aer yang Yohanis pake ko sarani sang Yesus, deng Yesus pung dara sandiri. Dong tiga-tiga tu, kasi tunju satu hal yang sama so'al Yesus.<bt>that is, God2's Spirit, the water which Yohanis used to baptise Yesus, and Yesus' own blood. All three of those things, show/point.out one thing which is the same about Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: the Spirit and the water"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: the Spirit and the water and the blood. And the three agree.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Kalo manusia yang jadi saksi, na, kotong biasa parcaya sang dia. Lebe-lebe lai kalo Tuhan Allah sandiri yang jadi saksi so'al Dia pung Ana sandiri. Padahal tiga hal ni, yang Tuhan su pake ko kasi tunju bukti bilang, Yesus tu, bukan cuma manusia biasa sa, ma Dia ju Kristus.<bt>If a human is the one who is a witness, na, we-inc usually believe him/her. And especially/even.more.so if God1 himself is the one who is a witness about His own Child. In.actual.fact these three things, are what God2 has used to show evidence that that Yesus wasn't just an ordinary human, but He was also Kristus. [EXEG: NLT and CEV missed a couple higher level signals in the Gk. hinted at in Ex. Summ. discussion. so our rendering of last clause not only makes more sense, but also more tightly reflects the Gk. Ex. Summ. + higher-level cohesion]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan pung Ana changed to Yesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">Tuhan pung Ana changed to Yesus in v9 but it still is referred to by pronoun tu in v10.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Since we receive the testimony"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Since we receive the testimony of men, the testimony of God is greater, because it is the testimony of God, which he has testified about his Son.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Orang yang parcaya sang Tuhan pung Ana tu, dia pung arti bilang, itu orang su tarima Tuhan pung Kata-kata so'al itu Ana. Ma orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan, dia sama ke orang yang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah tu, tukang putar-balek!&gt;&gt; Deng bagitu, dia sonde tarima Tuhan pung Kata-kata so'al Tuhan pung Ana sandiri.<bt>A person who believes in that Child of God2's, that means, that person accepted God2's Words about that Child. But a person who doesn't believe in God2, s/he is the same as a person who speaks saying, &lt;&lt;God [+known ref], is a habitual twister-turner (=deceiver)!&gt;&gt; In that way, s/he does not accept God2's Words about God's own Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who believes in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who believes in the Son of God has the testimony in himself; the one who does not believe God, makes God a liar, because he has not believed in the testimony which God testified about his Son.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Tuhan pung Kata-kata pung isi bagini: Dia su kasi kotong idop yang batúl yang sonde tau putus-putus. Deng kotong dapa itu idop, tagal kotong parcaya sang Dia pung Ana.<bt>The content of God's Words are like this: He has given us true/real life which goes forever [NOTE: phrasing from gospel of John]. And we obtained that life, because we believe in His Child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: And this is the testimony,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: And this is the testimony, that God gave us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 3:36</note><v n="12" />Jadi orang yang ta'ika deng Tuhan Allah pung Ana, dapa idop tarús-tarús deng Dia. Ma orang yang sonde ta'ika deng Tuhan Allah pung Ana, sonde dapa idop bagitu.<bt>So (consequently), the person who is bound/linked with God1's Child, can live forever with Him. But the person who is not bound/linked with God's Child, does not get that life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: The one who has the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: The one who has the Son has life; the one who does not have the Son of God does not have life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Akurang ko Yohanis tulis ini surat?<bt>Why does Yohanis write this letter?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Beta tulis ini hal samua kasi bosong yang parcaya sang Tuhan Allah pung Ana, ko biar bosong tau batúl-batúl bilang, bosong dapa idop tarús-tarús.<bt>I write all these things to you who believe in God1's Child, so that you can truly/really know/understand that, you obtain/get/have eternal life (nominal interp)/can live forever (verbal interp).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: I write these things to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: I write these things to you that believe in the name of the Son of God, so that you may know that you have eternal life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tulis tamba so'al sambayang<bt>Yohanis writes in addition/further about prayer</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Kalo kotong sambayang sang Tuhan Allah deng minta apa sa yang iko Dia pung mau, na, kotong bisa yakin Dia dengar apa yang kotong minta.<bt>If we-inc pray to God1 and request whatever is according to His will/desire, na, we can be assured/convinced that He hears that which we request. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure it is ‘ask what according to his will’ rather than ‘pray according to his will’, so that the focus is on WHAT we ask for, rather than the magic formula of HOW we ask.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ean: whenever, indefinite kata to theleema"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ean: whenever, indefinite kata to theleema autou: in line with his plans, not a passive "que sera, sera".<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: And this is the confidence which we have toward him, that whatever we ask according to his will, he hears us.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Deng kalo kotong su yakin bagitu, kotong ju yakin, kotong tarima apa yang kotong minta dari Dia.<bt>And if we are convinced like that, we are convinced that we receive what we request/ask from Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ean: hypothetic &quot;if&quot;, not factual &quot;since&quot;?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ean: hypothetic "if", not factual "since"? Blass-Debrunner-Funk 372.1.a consider this use, which is with the indicative mode, as a vulgar substitution for "ei" or "epei", in which case it could be read as English "since". But the factuality is conveyed by the "if ... den" pair, not by substituting a Pidgin causal for the conditional. LITERALLY: And if we know that he hears us in whatever we ask, we know that we have the things which we asked from him.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Kalo lu dapa lia lu pung sodara ada bekin sala yang sonde bekin dia mati, lebe bae lu sambayang minta ko Tuhan Allah tolong sang lu pung sodara tu, ko dia salamat. Naa, beta pung maksud di sini, andia, ada sala yang sonde bekin orang mati. Deng ada sala yang bisa bekin orang mati. Ma beta sonde suru sambayang kalo ada sala bagitu.<bt>If you-sg get to see/encounter your sibling doing wrong which does not make him die, it's better/best for you to pray requesting God1 to help that sibling of yours, so that s/he is saved. Naa, my meaning here, is, there are wrong/s which do not make people die. And there are wrongs which can make people die. But I am not ordering to pray if there is wrong like that. [EXEG (JEG): mee pros thanaton: "leads to death" doesn't specify whether this is physical death or spiritual death. If it's tagged as spiritual, we're bringing up the Scholastic chimaera of man being able to cook up something so heinous that God can't forgive it, which is not too different from asking if God can make a rock so big he can't move it. If it's just physical, then it's the more obvious situation that if you rob a bank and get shot dead, praying for you isn't going to help. The rendering we have is no more and no less explicit than the Greek, and as such puts the ball in the theologians' court where it belongs.] [EXEG: First complication: Gk is “if anyone sees ... he (3s) should ask”. English translations (I believe, correctly) render this as “if anyone sees ... you (2s/p) should pray...” For genre reasons I believe it is correct in the Timor region lgs to use “If you (2s) see ... you (2s) should pray and ask...” vs. 14-15 are in 1pi, but here John is pushing for a specific application. TB is literal to the Gk here (3s in both instances), and it is entirely possible nobody would think of applying it to themselves. Second complication: Do you think it is clearly implied here that God will actually give that person life if they pray for that? In these Timor region lgs, ‘pray’ and ‘ask’ are manipulative verbs. Grammatically they obligatorily take the irrealis complementiser, not the realis complementisor that is available to most other speech act verbs. This is logical, because what is being asked or ordered has not yet been carried out. It is common cross linguistically. So check with the UNSs. I can't think of any other way of phrasing it without making really heavy information load. Dhao has 2 irrealis complementisers that can be used, and the one we've used here seems to imply that the request was fulfilled.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hamartia: without the article, not a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">hamartia: without the article, not a specific act, but generic. mee pros thanaton: doesn't specify whether this is physical death or spiritual death. If it's tagged as spiritual, we're bringing up the Scholastic chimaera of man being able to cook up something so heinous that God can't forgive it, which is not too different from asking if God can make a rock so big he can't move it. If it's just physical, then it's the more obvious situation that if you rob a bank and get shot dead, praying for you isn't going to help. The rendering we have is no more and no less explicit than the Greek, and as such puts the ball in the theologians' court where it belongs.<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: If anyone sees his brother commit a sin that does not lead to death, he should pray and God will give him life. I refer to those whose sin does not lead to death. There is a sin that leads to death. I am not saying that he should pray about that.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Di Tuhan Allah pung muka, samua hal yang tar bae yang kotong bekin dong, sala abis. Ma sonde samua sala yang bawa mati.<bt>In God2's face/view, everything which is not good that we do, is wrong [+emph/thorough]. But not all wrongs are those that bring death. [EXEG: against God. 2nd sent "But" from Ex.Sum. &amp; TN]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: All unrighteousness is sin, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: All unrighteousness is sin, and there is sin that does not lead to death.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis kasi inga ulang hal yang pantíng<bt>Yohanis reminds again about the important thing</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Orang yang su ba'akar di Tuhan Allah su sonde idop bekin sala lai, te Tuhan pung Ana ada jaga sang dia. Deng jahat pung ba'i su tar ontong sang dia lai.<bt>A person who is already rooted in God1 doesn't live doing wrong anymore, cuz God2's Child is watching.over/guarding him/her. And the grandfather of evil already doesn't win.over/surmount/advantage over him/her anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jahat pung ba'i: raja satan UNS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z">jahat pung ba'i: raja satan UNS answer</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: We know that everyone who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: We know that everyone who has been born from God does not continue sinning, but the Son of God keeps him, and the Evil One does not touch him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Kotong tau bilang, kotong ni, ba'akar di Tuhan Allah. Ma kotong ju tau bilang, jahat pung ba'i ada kuasa ko ator samua orang di ini dunya.<bt>We-inc know that we here, are rooted in God1. But we also know that the grandfather of evil has the power/authority to oversee/regulate/control all the people in this world. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ek tou theou: 2:16 suggests &quot;has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ek tou theou: 2:16 suggests "has the quality of". 3:10, 4:4, 4:6 could work with this interpretation, but I'm not sure that "now we same kine jalike God" gives the idea that God has made us be that way and he started it. en tooi poneerooi: This would be ambiguous if not for v. 18, which is ho poneeros, the evil person, rather than "evil" in the abstract, which would be neuter.<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: We know that we are from God, and the whole world lies in wickedness.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Kotong tau bilang, Tuhan Allah pung Ana su datang ko kasi kotong mangarti ini hal dong, ko biar kotong bisa kanál Tuhan Allah yang batúl. Sakarang kotong su bisa idop babae deng Dia, tagal kotong idop satu hati deng Dia pung Ana, Yesus Kristus. Te Dia tu, Tuhan Allah yang batúl ju. Deng Dia yang kasi orang idop tarús-tarús.<bt>We know that God1's Child has come to enable us to understand these things, so that we can know/be.acquainted the true/real God1. Now we are able to live in a reciprocally good relationship with Him, because we live one livered with His Child, Yesus Kristus. Cuz (elaboration) He is also the true/real God1. And He is the one who enables people to live forever. [EXEG: NLT: And now we are in God *because* we are in his Son, JC.] [NOTE to daughter translations: the exegesis of the early church fathers used this verse to form the creeds that says Jesus is very God of very God; also TB, HCE, NRSV, NLT, CEV, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ton aleethinon: because of the rest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">ton aleethinon: because of the rest of the verse, and the masculine gender, this means the True One or the True God. But "true god" is acrolectal. "Da One dass God fo real kine" is more likely to communicate. en tooi aleethinooi, en tooi hyiooi autou I. Kh.: there's no causal implication in the appositive. It's "related to the True God; specifically, to his Son"<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>autou: antecedent is tooi aleethinooi. houtos: In Greek, refers backward. But "dis" in Pidgin implies that the referent has not been identified yet. So it needs to be "dass" or "dat".<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>LITERALLY: We know that the Son of God has come, and has given us understanding so that we know the one who is true. We are in the true one, his Son Jesus Christ. This is the true God and eternal life.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ana-ana dong! Jaga bae-bae bosong pung idop. Jang sampe ada yang seti buang ko ganti Tuhan Allah di bosong pung hati.<bt>Children, é! Guard your lives carefully. May it not be that something shoves aside/elbows out of the way to replace God1 in your livers. [EXEG: idols = take God's place in your heart (NLT); clever facsimile (Message) also TH, Ex. Summ #1.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bagitu sa,<bt>That's all.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanis<bt>Yohanis</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teknia: like children to me (old"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 00:08:34Z" status="Information">teknia: like children to me (old apostle to church leaders) LITERALLY: Little children, guard yourselves from idols.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
  </book>
</bible>